on that note.. Why is it that someone can put their 2 cents worth in. But it is only a penny for their thoughts???? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scrub15@oklahomasoftball>Scrub15</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#8B0000>(6/13/03 10:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  45softball</span><hr size=1> I think you are forgetting to add that the feild umpire was hold his had up for time, because the runner on second had not make it back to second at the time, therefore the pitch that she popped up never actually took place. So the appeal was actually legal. Here's a question for you,  Why is it that everytime someone loses a game it is the umpires fault?  I do admit that there are some terrible umpires out there, but that is why Brian has all these umpire clinics to get in fresh new umpires and get rid of the ones that are constantly blowing calls.  If you think you can do better call him and sign up.  Believe me that is why i did it, and let me tell you, it is harder than it looks.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C0D9D9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> punchinjudy</span><br> <span class=usertitle>I need to register</span><br>   <font color=#8B0000>(6/13/03 2:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  umps</span><hr size=1> I admit I get on umpires. It is part of my competive nature. But in this case I agree with the red. Forget appeals and all the other crap. Get the call right. So what if one pitch has been thrown. Get it right. Nobody wants them to go back an inning. But whenever possible forget whatever rule you have to and get the call right. <br>
<br>
Same stuff happened to us at Joplin. Girl is given a extra courtesy foul. LF is yelling hey she is out. Umpire in the field is shaking his head yes, pitcher not paying attention throws the next pitch for a single. Did the red overturn it, no we didn't appeal before the next pitch. The red in field heard us in plenty of time and was agreeing with us. To me that is appeal enough. Homeplate ump says simply if you want that call go get a rulebook.  No one was on base he simply could have said my bad your right she is out. And not really changed the outcome of the game. But instead says you don't know what your talking about go get a rbook and prove it. <br>
<br>
Funny thing is it happened again against us a couple of innings later and the field up stepped up and corrected him. Guess who brought up the rulebook line. <br>
<br>
And as far as trying to be an umpire, That is the thing that upsets me the most. I did it 8 years of HS and college baseball to go along with what I have done at different softball leagues. No I didn't know every little knit picking rule. But I got calls right. If I missed something were it was clear I was wrong and I knew it I changed the call. Yes it got me in trouble a couple of times. But I promise you I was one umpire everybody wanted when they were playing a big game. I always felt if I was going to be there I was going to bust my butt to do the best I could. And I left my ego in the dressing room. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Dont understand</span><br> <span class=usertitle>I need to register</span><br>   <font color=#8B0000>(6/15/03 1:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Keep trying</span><hr size=1> The call was right, but why don't you tell the rest of the story. You got run ruled in 5 innings. There is not a lot of controversy in that. I realize a grand slam is demoralizing, but you did get your opportunity to score.<br>
Bottom line, Get over it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C0D9D9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=back4more>Back4More</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8B0000>(6/16/03 3:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: umps</span><hr size=1> I say there are always going to be questionable calls...so just go hit the ball. If you loose the game and it just happened to be on a bad note w/umpire then so be it. I can always look back at a play or two or an inning at bat and say hey we could have done better and his or her call wouldn't have had any bearing.<br>
<br>
P.S. was it me or did it seem like the boys in red had a few bad calls every game? Or what about the women in red...whew....in our game and a game I watched she was talked into anything. For such a big tourn (Jocksnitch) I thought they could have been better. LOL on that note the drunk might have been pretty good lol ...we will never know<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=45softball@oklahomasoftball>45softball</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#8B0000>(6/17/03 3:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: 45softball</span><hr size=1> JUST TO MAKE IT CLEAR... I AM NOT THE ONE WHO WALKED THE GIRL........ AND I DO THINK THAT SHE SHOULD HAVE WALKED THE FIRST TIME.... BUT I AM NOT CRYING ABOUT US SUCKING IT UP THAT NIGHT AND LOSING THE BALL GAME B/C NO MATTER WHAT THE CALL WAS THAT NIGHT WE PROBABLY WOULD HAVE LOST ANYWAY (IT WAS ONE OF THOSE NIGHTS) THE THING I AM UPSET ABOUT IS THE UMPIRING... AND THAT INCLUDES MAKING THE RIGHT CALL IN THE FIRST PLACE!!!!!!!!!!! OR FOR THAT MATTER WHEN A WRONG CALL IS MADE SUCK IT UP AND FOLLOW THE RULES AS LAID OUT IN THE BOOK INSTEAD OF MAKING THEM UP AS YOU GO!!!!!!! OH AND SCRUB 15 I AM A CERTIFIED ASA UMPIRE AND THE REASON I DON'T DO USSSA IS B/C OF THE LACK OF CONSISTENCY IN THE UMPIRING RANKS.....MOSTLY DUE TO LACK OF TRAINING!!!!!!!!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showPrevMessa